[{"id":"VR000074","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">An astronaut on a new planet is hanging various objects with different known masses one at a time from a spring scale. The astronaut records the mass of the object and the force readings from the spring scale in a data table and constructs a graph. The astronaut is interested in determining the gravitational field strength <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase g\"><math alttext=\"lowercase g\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> on the surface of this new planet. Which of the following indicates how the astronaut should construct a graph to determine <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase g\"><math alttext=\"lowercase g\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> of the new planet and identifies the characteristic of the graph that is equal to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase g\"><math alttext=\"lowercase g\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> ?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR000074_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Graph the force as a function of mass; the slope is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase g\"><math alttext=\"lowercase g\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Graph the force as a function of mass; the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"y\"><math alttext=\"y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>y</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>-intercept is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase g\"><math alttext=\"lowercase g\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Graph the mass as a function of force; the slope is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase g\"><math alttext=\"lowercase g\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Graph the mass as a function of force; the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"y\"><math alttext=\"y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>y</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>-intercept is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase g\"><math alttext=\"lowercase g\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Graph the force squared as a function of mass; the slope is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase g\"><math alttext=\"lowercase g\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>"],"answer":0}]